BEGIN:VCALENDAR
VERSION:2.0
PRODID:-//EOLkits//AWS Deprecations//EN
CALSCALE:GREGORIAN
METHOD:PUBLISH
X-WR-CALNAME:AWS Deprecation Deadlines (EOLkits)
X-WR-TIMEZONE:UTC
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:lambda-node.js-20-phase-1@eolkits
DTSTAMP:20260722T000000Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20270201
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20270202
SUMMARY:Lambda Node.js 20 Phase 1
DESCRIPTION:Node.js 20 Lambda runtime (Amazon Linux 2023) deprecated 2026-04-30. Per the AWS Lambda runtime deprecation table\, AWS blocks creating new nodejs20.x functions on 2027-02-01 and updating existing ones on 2027-03-03 — part of the synchronized Q1-2027 runtime-block cluster. Source: https://docs.aws.amazon.com/lambda/latest/dg/lambda-runtimes.html
URL:https://docs.aws.amazon.com/lambda/latest/dg/lambda-runtimes.html
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:amazon-linux-2-eol@eolkits
DTSTAMP:20260722T000000Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260630
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260701
SUMMARY:Amazon Linux 2 EOL
DESCRIPTION:Amazon Linux 2 reaches end of life. No more security patches\, AMI publishing\, or extras updates. Source: https://aws.amazon.com/blogs/aws/update-on-amazon-linux-2-end-of-life/
URL:https://aws.amazon.com/blogs/aws/update-on-amazon-linux-2-end-of-life/
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:lambda-python-3.9-eol@eolkits
DTSTAMP:20260722T000000Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20270201
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20270202
SUMMARY:Lambda Python 3.9 EOL
DESCRIPTION:Python 3.9 Lambda runtime (Amazon Linux 2) was deprecated on 2025-12-15 (no further security patches). Per the AWS Lambda runtime deprecation table\, AWS blocks creating new python3.9 functions on 2027-02-01 and blocks updating existing ones on 2027-03-03. Functions keep running\, but become unpatched and unmodifiable after the block dates. Source: https://docs.aws.amazon.com/lambda/latest/dg/lambda-runtimes.html
URL:https://docs.aws.amazon.com/lambda/latest/dg/lambda-runtimes.html
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:lambda-python-3.10-eol@eolkits
DTSTAMP:20260722T000000Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20270201
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20270202
SUMMARY:Lambda Python 3.10 EOL
DESCRIPTION:Python 3.10 Lambda runtime deprecated 2026-10-31. Per the AWS Lambda runtime deprecation table\, AWS blocks creating new python3.10 functions on 2027-02-01 and updating existing ones on 2027-03-03 — the same synchronized Q1-2027 block cluster as python3.8/3.9. Source: https://docs.aws.amazon.com/lambda/latest/dg/lambda-runtimes.html
URL:https://docs.aws.amazon.com/lambda/latest/dg/lambda-runtimes.html
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:lambda-python-3.11-eol@eolkits
DTSTAMP:20260722T000000Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20270731
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20270801
SUMMARY:Lambda Python 3.11 EOL
DESCRIPTION:Python 3.11 Lambda runtime deprecated 2027-06-30. Per the AWS Lambda runtime deprecation table\, AWS blocks creating new python3.11 functions on 2027-07-31 and updating existing ones on 2027-08-31. Source: https://docs.aws.amazon.com/lambda/latest/dg/lambda-runtimes.html
URL:https://docs.aws.amazon.com/lambda/latest/dg/lambda-runtimes.html
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:lambda-node.js-18-eol@eolkits
DTSTAMP:20260722T000000Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20270201
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20270202
SUMMARY:Lambda Node.js 18 EOL
DESCRIPTION:Node.js 18 Lambda runtime (Amazon Linux 2) deprecated 2025-09-01. Per the AWS Lambda runtime deprecation table\, AWS blocks creating new nodejs18.x functions on 2027-02-01 and updating existing ones on 2027-03-03 — part of the synchronized Q1-2027 runtime-block cluster. nodejs18.x is one of the most common runtimes still in production. Source: https://docs.aws.amazon.com/lambda/latest/dg/lambda-runtimes.html
URL:https://docs.aws.amazon.com/lambda/latest/dg/lambda-runtimes.html
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:lambda-python-3.8-eol@eolkits
DTSTAMP:20260722T000000Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20270201
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20270202
SUMMARY:Lambda Python 3.8 EOL
DESCRIPTION:Python 3.8 Lambda runtime (Amazon Linux 2) deprecated 2024-10-14. Per the AWS Lambda runtime deprecation table\, AWS blocks creating new python3.8 functions on 2027-02-01 and updating existing ones on 2027-03-03 — the same synchronized Q1-2027 block cluster as python3.9/3.10. Source: https://docs.aws.amazon.com/lambda/latest/dg/lambda-runtimes.html
URL:https://docs.aws.amazon.com/lambda/latest/dg/lambda-runtimes.html
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:imdsv1-enforcement@eolkits
DTSTAMP:20260722T000000Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20251231
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260101
SUMMARY:IMDSv1 Enforcement
DESCRIPTION:IMDSv1 access will be blocked by default on new instance launches. Source: https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AWSEC2/latest/UserGuide/configuring-instance-metadata-service.html
URL:https://docs.aws.amazon.com/AWSEC2/latest/UserGuide/configuring-instance-metadata-service.html
END:VEVENT
END:VCALENDAR
